article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 86, UC Davis 59
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Orlando Johnson scored 21 points, leading five UC Santa Barbara players in double figures, and the Gauchos rolled to an 86-59 victory over UC Davis Thursday night -- the 15th straight loss for the Aggies. Jaime Serna scored 18 points, Alan Williams had 14 points and 12 rebounds, Kyle Boswell scored 12 and James Nunnally finished with 11 points for the Gauchos (10-7, 5-2 Big West), who began a four-game road swing. Santa Barbara held a 45-23 edge on the boards. Tyler Les scored 16 points to lead the Aggies (1-18, 0-7). Les made two 3-pointers for a 6-4 lead, but it was all UCSB after that. Johnson scored 14 in the first half to help the Gauchos to a 48-29 halftime advantage. Eddie Miller scored 13 and Tyrell Corbin added 11 points for UC Davis, whose only win this season came against Division III UC Santa Cruz.
